The property was just gorgeous. I canâ€™t imagine how much different it looks a month later with Fall color in full force. The ceremony and reception both overlooked a lake. All night long people commented on how beautiful it was. And honestly, it was a perfect place for a wedding!

Several weeks before the wedding we did engagement photos in Holly. At that time Lauren showed me all of the things that she had prepared for the wedding. Let me tell you, Lauren is hard working and so creative. She had a vision for her wedding and I canâ€™t help but think that as she looked around during the wedding that she saw all of her dreams come true.

So let me tell you how I know this couple. Trent is my cousin on my husbandâ€™s side. Weâ€™ve watched him grow up. We love our Michigan family so much and have gone on numerous trips to Mackinac Island together and just have the BEST time when weâ€™re together. The first time we met Lauren was last Summer (2019). He was so shocked when he walked in and saw us. At that time we just knew that Lauren was the one for Trent. And after that we kind of awaited the day until they got engaged. And they did! ðŸ™‚

Trent and Lauren, I am so happy that it worked out for me to be with you on your wedding day. I love you both and am so thankful that God brought you together.

Much love,

Amy
